    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Triclinic borosilicate mineral group comprised of  Axinite-(Fe), Axinite-(Mg), Axinite-(Mn), and Tinzenite. Axinite without a sub-designation is not recognized as an individual mineral species. The group has its name after the generic name axinite first introduced in 1797 by the French mineralogist Rene Just Haüy.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
